Paul , Prince Saradine , A vos ordres , said the venerable person politely , lifting a glass of sherry . 
I live here very quietly , being a domestic kind of fellow and for the sake of modesty I am called Mr. Paul , to distinguish me from my unfortunate brother Mr. Stephen . 
He died , I hear , recently in the garden . 
Of course , it is not my fault if enemies pursue him to this place . 
It is owing to the regrettable irregularity of his life . 
He was not a domestic character . 
